21/01/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Muslim communities in Southeast Europe launched festivities related to the religious holiday Kurban Bajram on Thursday (20 January). 
The day was an official holiday in Turkey, Albania and Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). 
In BiH, dawn prayers and celebrations were held in Sarajevo, Bihac, Trebinje, Tuzla and Zenica. 
In Macedonia, Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski visited the Islamic Religious Community office to extend his congratulations. 
Festivities also took place in Bulgaria, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro. 
(ATA, Fena, PBS BiH, Makfax - 20/01/05)
